const documentText = String.raw`This skills4export.com Cookie Policy (“Cookie Policy") describes the different types of cookies, pixels, local storage objects, log files, and other similar technologies (“cookies”) we use on the skills4export.com Platform.

About Cookies
Cookies are text files that store information on the browser of your device when you visit a website. These text files are read by websites and help identify your device, remember your preferences, and improve your experience. We use the following categories of cookies:

First Party and Third Party Cookies. First party cookies are served directly by us to your browser or device. Third party cookies are served by a third party on the skills4export.com Platform and collect data for that third party.
Persistent and Session Cookies. Persistent cookies remain on your device for a specific duration. Session cookies only last for the session while your browser window is open and are deleted once you close your browser.
How We Use Cookies:
We use the following types of cookies for the purposes outlined below:

Strictly Necessary Cookies. These cookies are necessary to make the skills4export.com Platform work and will automatically deploy on your device or browser. We use these cookies to enable core website functionality features, including security, authentication, and network management. You cannot block or disable these cookies.
Functional Cookies. These cookies help personalize and improve your experience on skills4export.com by remembering the choices you make. We use these cookies to show that you’re logged into the skills4export.com Platform, remember your settings (e.g., language preferences, region, text size), remember if we've already asked you if you want to fill in a survey, and show embedded content.
Performance Cookies. These cookies help us understand how you engage with the skills4export.com Platform and learn what content is popular. These cookies collect information that allow us to analyze which parts of the skills4export.com Platform users are engaging with and find useful. We also use these cookies for web analytics, to perform traffic sourcing, measure site performance, and test new designs.
Advertising Cookies. These cookies are used to display targeted advertisements to you based on your browsing history and interests on the skills4export.com Platform, as well other websites, apps and online services. These cookies help us serve relevant advertisements based on your personal interests. We also use these cookies to improve how we deliver personalized content and measure advertising campaigns on the skills4export.com Platform.
skills4export.com Pixel and Third Party Service Providers:
We work with third party advertising and analytics service providers to display relevant advertisements to you while on the skills4export.com Platform and on third party websites. These third party service providers may embed skills4export.com’s Pixel (“Pixels”) on their websites, which allows us to collect browsing information across sites to display relevant content and advertisements to you. Our Pixels also provide advertisement measurement and performance data for our third party service providers.

Our Pixels collect IP address, date and time of your visit, user agent, cookie IDs, URL, time zone, and other browser-level data. We may also share this information anonymously and in the aggregate with our third party service providers. Please visit our Pixel Privacy Terms for more information and visit this page to learn how to opt out of Pixels tracking.

How to Manage Cookies:
You can block, delete, or disable cookies on your device at any time by changing your preferences in your browser or device, as described below. However, doing so may limit your ability to view certain pages on the skills4export.com Platform.

Browser Device Settings. To learn more about how to manage cookies, visit aboutcookies.org or the browser instructions for Firefox, Chrome, or Safari.
Mobile Device Settings. iOS’ Limit Ad Tracking and Android’s Opt out of Ads Personalization settings allow you to have greater control over the app activity data that is shared with third party advertisers.
Third Party Opt-Outs. The online advertising industry offers resources to help you opt out of certain advertising cookies. For more information visit the Network Advertising Initiative, the Digital Advertising Alliance, the European Interactive Digital Advertising Alliance, or the Digital Advertising Alliance of Canada.
Google Analytics. You can download the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on to prevent data collection via Google Analytics. Visit Google’s Analytics Help Page for more information.
Contact Us:
Please contact us at privacy@skills4export.com if you have questions about this Cookie Policy. For more information about our privacy practices, please review our Privacy Policy.`
